b'' b'' b'greetings fellow motorcycle roadracing enthusiasts!' b'' b'background' b'----------' b'' b'the racing listserver (boogie.ebay.sun.com) contains discussions' b'devoted to racing and racing-related topics. this is a pretty broad' b'interest group. individuals have a variety of backgrounds: motojournalism,' b'roadracing from the perspective of pit crew and racers, engineering,' b'motosports enthusiasts.' b'' b'the size of the list grows weekly. we are currently at a little' b'over one hundred and eighty-five members, with contributors from' b'new zealand, australia, germany, france, england, canada' b'finland, switzerland, and the united states.' b'' b'the list was formed (october in response to a perceived need' b'to both provide technical discussion of riding at the edge of' b'performance (roadracing) and to improve on the very low signal-to-noise' b'ratio found in rec.motorcycles. anyone is free to join.' b'' b'discussion is necessarily limited by the rules of the list to' b'issues related to racing motorcycles and is to be "flame-free".' b'' b'how to get the daily distribution' b'---------------------------------' b'' b'you are welcome to subscribe. to subscribe send your request to:' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'traffic currently runs between five and twenty-five messages per day' b'(depending on the topic).' b'' b'nb: please do _not_ send your subscription request to the' b'list directly.' b'' b'after you have contacted the list administrator, you will receive' b'an rsvp request. please respond to this request in a timely manner' b'so that you can be added to the list. the request is generated in' b'order to insure that there is a valid mail pathway to your site.' b'' b'upon receipt of your rsvp, you will be added to either the daily' b'or digest distribution (as per your initial request).' b'' b'how to get the digest distribution' b'----------------------------------' b'' b"it is possible to receive the list in 'digest'ed form (ie. a" b'single email message). the roadracing digest is mailed out' b'whenever it contains enough interesting content. given the' b'frequency of postings this appears to be about every other' b'day.' b'' b'should you wish to receive the list via digest (once every' b'30-40k or so), please send a subscription request to:' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'how to post to the list' b'-----------------------' b'' b'this is an open forum. to post an article to the list, send to:' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'depending on how mail is set up at your site you may or may' b'not see the mail that you have posted. if you want to see it' b"(though this isn't necessarily a guarantee that it went out)" b'you can include a "metoo" line in your .mailrc file (on unix' b'based mail systems).' b'' b'bounces' b'-------' b'' b"because i haven't had the time (or the inclination to replace" b'the list distribution mechanism) we still have a problem with' b'bounces returning to the poster of a message. occasionally,' b'sites or users go off-line (either leaving their place of' b'employment prematurely or hardware problems) and you will receive' b'bounces from the race list. check the headers carefully, and' b'if you find that the bounce originated at sun (from whence i' b'administer this list) contact me through my administration' b'' b'other lists' b'-----------' b'' b'or uunet!watmath!thinkage!harley-request' b'(in body of message write: subscribe euro-moto)' b'' b'' b'thanks, be seeing you,' b'rich (race list administrator)' b'' b'--' b'stefan fielding-isaacs office/fax' b'dba art science "books by design" voice/pager' b'ama/ccs b'* currently providing consulting writing services to: gain technology, verity 